The paper deals with property testing, which is a topic in theoretical computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The use of adaptivity in property testing suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CC (computational complexity) or cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The focus on quantifying the degree of adaptivity and proving an adaptivity hierarchy theorem suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IT (information theory) or cs.LG (machine learning). Finally, the mention of testing natural properties of graphs suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
